date

Class Date

  • java.lang.Object
    • date.Date
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Date>, java.util.Comparator<Date>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PioneerDate

    public class Date
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Date>, java.util.Comparator<Date>, java.io.Serializable
    This class creates a Date Object that can be used to hold any valid date that can exist. It can take in three ints in the constructor to set the date if valid or it will throw an error with details about what the error is.
    Author:
    Brandon Bonebrake
